                <h1>Understanding Background Radiation Levels: Risks & Sources</h1>
                <p>Background radiation levels refer to the natural ionizing radiation present in the environment, originating from cosmic rays, terrestrial sources, and even radon gas. Understanding these levels is crucial for assessing exposure risks. Typically measured in microsieverts, global averages can vary but generally remain low, posing minimal health hazards.</p>
